name: The Peking Acrobats
description: Known for redefining audience perceptions of Chinese acrobatics with daring maneuvers, trick-cycling, precision tumbling, and juggling. They have also been featured in films like "Ocean's Eleven."

name: Shen Yun Performing Arts
description: Presents classical Chinese dance and music, aiming to revive 5,000 years of divinely inspired Chinese culture. While not solely an acrobatics troupe, their performances often incorporate elements of traditional Chinese arts

name: Chinese Acrobats of Hebei
description: Features unique acts such as Chinese Poles, Foot Juggling, and Towering Chair Balance, combined with martial arts and oriental soundtracks

name: National Acrobats of The People's Republic of China (China National Acrobatic Troupe)
description: One of the first national performing arts troupes in China, known for a repertoire of award-winning acts like "Slack Wire" and "Diabolo."

name: Li Liu (Solo Performer)
description: A solo performer specializing in hand balancing, plate spinning, artistic cycling, and ribbon dancing, who also incorporates Chinese language and culture into her shows
